<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-493-805  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 493 805.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Fal 1990 v15 n11 p97(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Programming 32-bit OS/2: working with OS/2 2.0 SDK. (SoftwareDevelopment Kit)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Heller, Martin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The early version of Microsoft Corp's $2,600 OS/2 2.0 SoftwareDevelopment Kit (SDK) provides a good overview of the forthcomingOS/2 2.0 operating system (OS) and a viable tool for developingapplications for that environment.andP;  The single-user, 32-bit,multitasking OS features support for multiple programming models(including MS-DOS, OS/2 1.2 and Windows), multiple virtual DOSmachines (MVDMs), linear memory model, paged virtual memory, the80386 instruction set, high performance file system, and extendedfile attributes and long filenames.andP;  Other aspects of OS/2 2.0discussed include its 32-bit kernel application programminginterface, semaphores, threads and processes, queues and anonymouspipes, use of Apple's TrueType B-spline font outlines; and SystemMigration Kit.andP;  OS/2 2.0 should motivate IBM-type personalcomputer users to replace MS-DOS with OS/2.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   OS/2 2.0 (Operating system) (design and construction)OS/2 Software Development Kit (Program development software)(usage).andO;Topic:     Program Development Tools32-BitSpecificationsEvaluationComparisonOS-2 (Operating system).andO;Feature:   illustrationprogram.andO;Caption:   OS/2 1.x supports memory objects larger than 64Kbytes, but notefficiently. (program)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>